      • apply

        public <I extends Input> Selector<I> apply(boolean support_multi_stage,
                                           java.lang.String field,
                                           Selector<I> sel,
                                           Form form,
                                           java.util.HashMap fixtures)
        Description copied from interface: FieldConstraint
        Mutate a Selector based on other form fields. Normally this requires the value of the input to have a fixed value e.g. an UnmodifiableInput, a ListInput with a single valid option or a suppressed field. If the prerequisite fields are not fixed or not present then this method can return null to request an additional form stage be introduced. The form builder should then retry this field in subsequent stages (where previous fields will be locked). Fixed values are copied into the fixtures map. This also can contain values for supressed fields. Care needs to be taken with pre-requisites that are optional. Ideally if support_multi_stage is false the method should add a corresponding FormValidator to the form instead and return the original Selector
        Specified by:
        apply in interface FieldConstraint
        Type Parameters:
        I - type of Input
        Parameters:
        support_multi_stage - Does surrounding context support multi-stage
        field - Field that Selector is for
        sel - Selector
        form - Form being built.
        fixtures - HashMap of fixed field data. This can include supressed fields. note values of optional fields may be null.
        Returns:
        mutated Selector or null to request an additional form stage.
